<br>
My personal theory is thus......<br>
<br>
on Sebilis/Akheva/Velks type mobs I slow early because I can stun them if I get aggro on a resist.<br>
<br>
on things such as Xin Thall Centiens which can be up to level 58, and mobs in Umbral which are all 54+ I wait till I at least see some damage before trying to slow.  It takes 3+ resisted slows for me to get aggro. typically after a mob has visible damage.<br>
<br>
Thanks for all the input folks.  I like hearing about other play styles and techniques.  Knowledge is power. <p>Stewwy (aka The little yellow bus)<br>
